name: NoEscape
description:
NoEscape is a merge model I've made trying to recreate the DazStudio look, near realism but not quite.

I've used adetailer for the faces, this bypass the need to upscale and inpaint trick.

Save the preview images as jpeg and you can load them inside Automatic1111 to get the full prompt and adetailer settings.

Prompt for the main image including adetailer settings

professional photo of a (dutch woman:1.1),
she is wearing clown costume and she has very long purple hair,
detailed skin, detailed eyes, detailed clown makeup,
inside dusty circus arena,
volumetric fog, volumetric dust,
photo made with Canon EOS in natural style photography,
popular on artstation, popular on deviantart, popular on flicker
Negative prompt: bad-artist, 3D, anime, nsfw, nude, naked, asian, jewelry, backlight, watermark, Bindi, hat
Steps: 50, Sampler: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras, CFG scale: 6.5, Seed: 1213408215, Size: 512x768, Model hash: 9bbf2b95f3, Model: NoEscape, Denoising strength: 0.34, ADetailer model: face_yolov8n.pt, ADetailer prompt: "professional photo of a (dutch woman:1.1), she is wearing clown costume and she has very long purple hair, detailed skin, detailed eyes, detailed clown makeup, volumetric fog, volumetric dust, photo made with Canon EOS in natural style photography, popular on artstation, popular on deviantart, popular on flicker", ADetailer negative prompt: "bad-artist, 3D, anime, nsfw, nude, naked, asian, jewelry, backlight, watermark, Bindi, hat", ADetailer confidence: 0.3, ADetailer dilate/erode: 32, ADetailer mask blur: 4, ADetailer denoising strength: 0.4, ADetailer inpaint only masked: True, ADetailer inpaint padding: 32, ADetailer ControlNet model: control_v11p_sd15_inpaint [ebff9138], ADetailer version: 23.6.1.post0, Hires upscale: 1.602, Hires steps: 60, Hires upscaler: 4x-UltraSharp, ControlNet 0: "preprocessor: inpaint_global_harmonious, model: control_v11p_sd15_inpaint [ebff9138], weight: 1.0, starting/ending: (0.0, 1.0), resize mode: ResizeMode.INNER_FIT, pixel perfect: True, control mode: ControlMode.BALANCED, preprocessor params: (512, 64, 64)", Version: v1.3.1
